<div class="p text-right font-secondary"><a href="table/T3/" class="usa-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open in a new tab</a></div></section><section class="tw xbox font-sm" id="T4"><h4 class="obj_head">Table 4.</h4>
<div class="caption p"><p>Birth and death rates stratified by different concentrations of antibody, where 
<span xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><math id="M56" overflow="linebreak"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><msubsup><mi mathvariant="bold">z</mi><mi>i</mi><mo>′</mo></msubsup><msub><mi mathvariant="bold-italic">θ</mi><mi>λ</mi></msub></mrow></msup></math></span> and 
<span xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><math id="M57" overflow="linebreak"><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><msubsup><mi mathvariant="bold">z</mi><mi>i</mi><mo>′</mo></msubsup><msub><mi mathvariant="bold-italic">θ</mi><mi>μ</mi></msub></mrow></msup></math></span>. We obtained asymptotic standard errors by applying the delta method to the asymptotic variance matrix of our estimate of <strong><em>θ</em></strong>. Note that the birth rate <em>λ</em> decreases much more rapidly than death rate <em>μ</em> as antibody concentration increases.</p></div>
